description.narrative:
This is a core funding to Woman's Resource Center (WRC), a local women&rsquo;s organization established in 2008, engaged in women&rsquo;s empowerment &ndash; helping women to make informed decisions and improve their lives and those of their children and families, particularly to address common women&rsquo;s issues such as gender-based violence, sexual and reproductive health, parenting and financial literacy.
The strategic objectives of the project are:&nbsp;
-&nbsp;Empower women and their families to break the culture of silence and access their rights;
- Provide vulnerable women with informal educational workshops on economic empowerment, gender equality, personal safety and positive parenting;
- Engage community action among proactive civil society members to participate in leadership training; to become WRC&rsquo;s advocates;
-&nbsp;Strengthen collaboration and partnership between NGOs, service providers and authorities for beneficiaries and clients to receive the required holistic support.
WRC&rsquo;s strategy is still crafted on annual basis, but are generally geared towards long-term services including: emotional support, information and referral program, informal education on health, women&rsquo;s rights, positive parenting, financial literacy and multimedia skills and other outreach education for school students and villagers.&nbsp;The expected results are that&nbsp;women and men including victims of domestic violence and other type of marginalized group benefited from regular support and educational programs of the center.&nbsp;
Rights holders who are WRC&rsquo;s direct beneficiaries are mostly women aged 14-45, although the center also receive male clients.
Currently WRC operates in Siem Reap Province only with one commune identified as one pilot target area, Svay Dongkum.
WRC&rsquo;s stakeholders, particularly in its referral service, include a whole range of service providers in legal, health, employment, vocational training, organizational development and business sectors.&nbsp;
